id: pm-z436
title: "As an agent on a minutes-old scratch project, pm init, quick-capture create, and next are near-zero ceremony and token-cheap at three-item scale"
description: ""
type: Story
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,onboarding,small-scale,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:36:18.776Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T23:36:18.776Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "A documented scratch/minimal metadata profile lets pm create <type> <title> succeed with no further flags and zero validate warnings; the full init -> create x3 -> next -> close round trip is covered by an e2e test asserting a bounded total token footprint (measured via the pm-a22j corpus method) and bounded wall-clock latency; pm context/next on a sub-10-item workspace produce output whose token cost is proportional to the workspace, with no fixed large envelope; the quickstart doc shows the scratch flow in under ten lines; governance defaults never require ceremony the scratch profile has not opted into"
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[4]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-4k6b,related,"2026-07-06T23:36:18.776Z",null,null
  pm-cu1i,related,"2026-07-06T23:36:18.776Z",null,null
